Lars,

Can you browse through the French pages and 

1) wrap anything that needs to be translated with Lang.getLabel(), as below.
2) add a prefix to any path hard coded or generated via a kit:find, as below (but leave the Navigation package alone, K will look at that). This includes, the global navigation, footer and breadcrumb.

After that you'll need to look at:

- Excluding sections that don't have French equivalents from the French pages (Blog, Commenting, Registration link)
- Changing the en/fr links at the top 
- Search pages

(but lets catch up before you start on those, as they will involve some discussion, me or K might be able to help you with them or indeed Janos)

Can you keep a list (Google docs?) of anything that appears problematic, for starters I imagine it's going to contain a list like this:

- English written out in Javascript
- English text in images
- English in includes (do we need specific French includes or do we pull in English ones)
- What about Map?

Assuming this is mainly what you will be working on for the next week, but can you keep track of time spent and let me know (not via this ticket) as we need to bill for the total time spent on French / let Liz and Morag know how much we have spent so far.

Thanks

Jamie

I have created a new "Lang" package that currently contains the following two methods:

    getLabel: function(name, locale, en)
    // A wrapper around kit.getLabel()
    // This wrapper is so that we can display a warning message when
    // in "preview" mode.
    // In "publish" mode, if there's no value found for the specified
    // locale, we just output the english value. Which is wrong but
    // better than nothing and better than an error message.
    // You should only ever need to call:
    //   Lang.getLabel("Label name");
    // "locale" will get derived from the current page.
    // "en" never needs to be set (afaics).
    
    prefix: function (p)
    // A convenience method, which returns "" or "fr/",
    // depending on the language of the current page.
    // You can use it as follows:
    //   <form action="{Lang.prefix() + 'search.php'}"> ...
    // If you are on a french page, the form will go to fr/search.php.
    // If you are on an english page, the form will go to search.php.
    // The "p" parameter is only really useful if you want to use from
    // the console (i.e. if you don't have a current page).


As a proof of concept, I have amended the following components:

"Include - Sports people" (example of how to use Lang.getLabel)
Was:
    <strong>Name:</strong><content:text id="person-name"/><br />
    <strong>Date of birth:</strong><content:text id="dob" name="dob" schema="hyperlink" /><br />
    <strong>Country:</strong><content:text id="country" name="country"/><br />
Now:
    <strong><?js=Lang.getLabel("Name")?>:</strong><content:text id="person-name"/><br />
    <strong><?js=Lang.getLabel("Date of birth")?>:</strong><content:text id="dob" name="dob" schema="hyperlink" /><br />
    <strong><?js=Lang.getLabel("Country")?>:</strong><content:text id="country" name="country"/><br />

"nav-searchbox" (example of how to use Lang.getLabel & Lang.prefix)
Was:
    <form id="header-2012-search-form" action="search.php" method="get">
        <label for="header-2012-search-box" class="hide-content" >Search</label>
        <input id="header-2012-search-box" type="text" class="text smartInput" value="Search" name="q" />
        <input type="image" class="submit" id="searchSubmit" alt="Search button" src="images/presentation/blue-header-submit.png" />
    </form>
Now:
    <form id="header-2012-search-form" action="{Lang.prefix() + 'search.php'}" method="get">
        <label for="header-2012-search-box" class="hide-content" ><?js=Lang.getLabel('Search')?></label>
        <input id="header-2012-search-box" type="text" class="text smartInput" value="{Lang.getLabel('Search')}" name="q" />
        <input type="image" class="submit" id="searchSubmit" alt="{Lang.getLabel('Search button')}" src="images/presentation/blue-header-submit.png" />
    </form>

